SIMPLE: measurable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Measurable
<hw>Meas"ur*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>mesurable</ets>, L. <ets>mensurabilis</ets>. See <er>Measure</er>,
and cf. <er>Mensurable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being measured; susceptible of
mensuration or computation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Moderate; temperate; not excessive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of his diet <qex>measurable</qex> was he.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Meas"ur*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Meas"ur*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet do it <qex>measurably</qex>, as it becometh Christians.</q>
<rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>measure</ent>⟦br⟧
